ofile?language=EN>Hibashira</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/9/02 9:08:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=570.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What lvl to start quadding?</span><hr size=1> 34 gives you circle of force, a way better ae nuke than what you have at 29, and more importantly, mana efficient.  Unless you are really twinked, you are likely to run out of mana at 29. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uscalem.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scalem</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/10/02 2:37:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=570.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What lvl to start quadding?</span><hr size=1>  You can actually begin quading earlier than 34. Its just alot easier at 34 with CoF.  At 24, you can full tilt kite in Lake with CoL. Just gather yourself 4 mobs by either using your SoTF or proximity aggro. Bunch them up and let loose. This is going fairly well for me and I dont run OOM on the goblins, but I do have a 217 INT with about +220mana from gear. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uchiriko37.showPublicProfile?language=EN>chiriko37</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/10/02 10:02:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=570.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What lvl to start quadding?</span><hr size=1> yeah, I quadded goblins 24-30 in Lake of Ill Omen. Great xp, pretty easy to do, and a great way to learn. no snare needed!<br><br>-Chiriko <p><center>Chiriko, lvl 56 Evoker, Innoruuk<br>Lux et Veritas<br><img src="http://new.comfluent.net/images/chiriko2.jpg"><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=374829">Ghetto Magelo-style</a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ubranamanstarbinder.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Branaman Starbinder</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/11/02 4:48:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=570.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://httpd.chello.nl/j.wensveen1/images/ofo2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What lvl to start quadding?</span><hr size=1> Fire beetles and spiderlings at level 4 with Icestrike and alot of mana gear added. SoW needed.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucarneab.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Carne AB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/11/02 10:29:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=570.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What lvl to start quadding?</span><hr size=1> I started at 27 in loio, new server very untwinked about 160int and no mana items. I didn't start snaring till after I left sk gnolls at 36. Sk was pretty easy with either ae spell. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=247012> Vani Lala</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ustryyfblackness.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stryyf Blackness</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/16/02 11:07:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=570.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Learning to quad</span><hr size=1>  I am a twink wizzy on lanys have 255 int and about +300 mana now i use a zland heart as my rimary hand <br>so i got a lil regen but i am having a terible time try'n to kite my main is a Ranger and maybe i am try'n to kite to much like a ranger but any help?<br>I cant seem to find the runes for COL either =( <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udaxilsolshok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daxil Solshok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/1/02 8:03:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=570.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://daxil.htmlplanet.com/images/eq000093.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Learning to quad</span><hr size=1> Optimally the best time to start kiting is 34 and Circle of Force, but then sometime in the 40s you have to stop again as that AE becomes obsolete, then 51 you start up again with Pillar of Frost. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uthanawhisperblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thana Whisperblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/17/02 6:03:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=570.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.lara.dk/LittleDevil4.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Learning to quad</span><hr size=1> I started to quad at level 29 when I got the snare spell. I practiced on green/light blue aviaks in sk, and at level 30 I moved to Marus Seru. <br>I started to kite 2 at a time, and when I felt safe, I moved to 3 at a time, and finally 4. I had many troubles pulling before I got my flux staff, since I pulled with snare, and snare wore off before I had mobs grouped etc. But then I got some friends to help me get the flux staff and I saw the light.<br>Pull with that instant click debuff, round up mobs and get a good distance and cast snare, Its cake when its learned really <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>Now I am quadding in Eastern wastes, Ulthorks are great exp at 35+.<br><br>Obinki, 37 Wiz <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showNextMessage?topicID=570.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=570.topic&index=8><img src=http://www.graffe.com/messageboard/add_reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top">